OL,3,CSir Bobby Charlton's legacy lives on,
OL,4,Cone year on from legend's death
OL,6,FHe played 758 games and scored 249
OL,7,Fgoals during his 17 years at Old
OL,8,FTrafford.
OL,10,FSir Bobby was also a member of the
OL,11,FEngland team that won the World Cup in
OL,12,F1966 which was when he also became the
OL,13,Fwinner of the Ballon d'Or.
OL,15,FHe remains England's third-highest
OL,16,Fgoal scorer.
